9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 276, L.D. 592, “An Act to Amend the
10 Laws Governing the Crime of Endangering the Welfare of a Child”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, to Study Laws Regarding Endangering the Welfare of a Child'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
14 'Sec. 1. Office of Child and Family Services to convene working group.
15 Resolved: That the Department of Health and Human Services, Office of Child and
16 Family Services, established in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 22, section 5308 and
17 referred to in this resolve as "the office," shall convene a working group with broad
18 representation to study the laws regarding endangering the welfare of a child.
19 Sec. 2. Membership. Resolved: That the working group under section 1 consists
20 of, at a minimum, the following members:
21 1. The director of the office or the director's designee;
22 2. The Commissioner of Public Safety or the commissioner's designee;
23 3. The chair of the Criminal Law Advisory Commission or the chair's designee;
24 4. The Victim Services Coordinator of the Office of Victim Services within the
25 Department of Corrections or the coordinator's designee;
26 5. A representative of a statewide organization advocating on behalf of children;
27 6. A representative of a statewide organization with expertise in the child welfare
28 system advocating on behalf of children;
29 7. A representative of a statewide organization representing domestic violence victims;
30 8. A representative of a statewide association representing prosecutors;
31 9. A representative of a statewide association representing criminal defense attorneys;
32 10. A representative of a statewide organization advocating for civil liberties;
Page 1 - 132LR1475(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 276, L.D. 592
1 11. A representative of a statewide association representing law enforcement officers;
2 and
3 12. A representative of a statewide organization representing individuals with
4 substance use disorder.
5 Sec. 3. Working group duties. Resolved: That the working group under section 1
6 shall, at a minimum, study the following issues:
7 1. Current developments in state law as they relate to endangering the welfare of a
8 child, including, but not limited to, the crimes of assault, manslaughter and endangering
9 the welfare of a child, and whether those current state laws are sufficiently protective;
10 2. Whether establishing a Class C or higher crime for endangering the welfare of a
11 child when it results in serious bodily injury would deter actions that endanger the welfare
12 of a child;
13 3. Whether establishing a Class C or higher crime for endangering the welfare of a
14 child when it results in serious bodily injury would deter parents from seeking medical
15 assistance for their child; and
16 4. How other states' criminal statutes establish crimes for endangering the welfare of
17 a child and the efficacy of those laws.
18 Sec. 4. Report. Resolved: That, by January 1, 2026, the office shall submit a report
19 that includes the findings and recommendations of the working group under section 1,
20 including suggested legislation, for presentation to the Joint Standing Committee on
21 Criminal Justice and Public Safety. The committee may submit legislation based on the
22 report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
23 Sec. 5. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
24 appropriations and allocations are made.
25 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
26 Office of Child and Family Services - Central 0307
27 Initiative: Provides one-time funding for contracted services to facilitate a working group
28 and prepare a report.
