COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 276, L.D. 592
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill with
33 a resolve. The amendment directs the Department of Health and Human Services, Office
44 of Child and Family Services to convene a working group to study the laws regarding
55 endangering the welfare of a child. In conducting the study, the working group must study
66 developments in state law regarding endangering the welfare of a child; whether
77 establishing a felony-level crime for endangering the welfare of a child when it results in
88 serious bodily injury will deter actions that endanger the welfare of a child or if it would
99 deter parents from seeking medical assistance for their child; and how other states' criminal
1100 statutes establish crimes for endangering the welfare of a child. The office is required to
1111 submit a report by January 1, 2026 to the Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice
1122 and Public Safety, which may submit legislation to the Second Regular Session of the
1133 132nd Legislature. The amendment adds an appropriations and allocations section.
